KANSAS CITY, Kan. (AP) — Daniel Salloi scored two goals to spark Sporting Kansas City to a 2-1 victory over the Colorado Rapids on Wednesday.Salloi gave Sporting KC (3-7-3) a 1-0 lead in the 24th minute. Lucas Esteves pulled the Rapids (4-5-3) even with a goal in the 29th minute.Salloi’s game-winner came five minutes into the second half.The Rapids outshot Sporting KC 10-6 and had a 3-2 edge in shots on goal.Tim Melia had two saves for Sporting KC.___The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.